S_n/\sqrt{n} \to Z
n
A = S_n/\sqrt{n}
B = S_{2n}/\sqrt{2n}
Z
C=(\sqrt{2}B - A)/(\sqrt{2}-1)
Z
\varepsilon > 0
n
A
C
\Pr[A > 0, C > 0] = \Pr[A>0]\cdot \Pr[C>0] \leq (\Pr[Z > - \varepsilon] + \varepsilon)^2 = (1/2 + O(\varepsilon))^2 = 1/4 + O(\varepsilon).
\Pr[A > 0 | Z > \varepsilon] > 1 - \varepsilon
\Pr[C > 0 | Z > \varepsilon] > 1 - \varepsilon
\Pr[A > 0, Z >0 | Z > \varepsilon] > 1 - 2\varepsilon
 \Pr[A > 0, Z >0]\geq  \Pr[A > 0, Z >0 | Z > \varepsilon]\cdot \Pr[Z > \varepsilon] \geq (1-2\varepsilon) \Pr[Z > \varepsilon] = 1 - O(\varepsilon).
